{title: Revive Us Again}
{artist: Willie Nelson}
{composer: Written by William P. Mackay and John J. Husband}

[3/4 time]
[C]We praise Thee O God for the Son of Thy love
For Jesus Who [F]died [C]and is [G7]now gone above
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory halle[F]lu[C]jah a[G7]men
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory re[F]vive [G7]us a[C]gain
All glory and praise to the lamb that was slain
Who hath borne all our [F]sins [C]and hath [G7]cleansed every stain
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory halle[F]lu[C]jah a[G7]men
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory re[F]vive [G7]us a[C]gain
All glory and praise to the God of all grace
Who hast brought us and [F]sought [C]us and [G7]guided our ways
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory halle[F]lu[C]jah a[G7]men
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory re[F]vive [G7]us a[C]gain
Revive us again fill each heart with Thy love
May each soul be re[F]kindled [C]with [G7]fire from above
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory halle[F]lu[C]jah a[G7]men
[C]Halle[F]lu[C]jah Thine the glory re[F]vive [G7]us a[C]gain